    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature, then boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml [<span class=\"text-purple\">250ml</span>] [<span class=\"text-danger\">300ml</span>] <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Tip: Chop them in different ways to create an interesting texture!</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>soft cheese</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> creamy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>steak</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked steak</strong> to a plate and rest until serving</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of vegetable oil if the pan looks dry!</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, discarding the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have softened, add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>creamy stock</strong> with your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>stroganoff sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> rested steak</strong> finely on a clean board</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rump-steak-and-chestnut-mushroom-stroganoff-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced steak</strong> over the <strong>stroganoff sauce</strong> with the<strong> cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
